    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use <kbd>cmd</kbd> + <kbd>,</kbd> for Mac or <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Alt</kbd> + <kbd>S</kbd> for Windows/Linux to pull up the Settings dialog. Then, go to &quot;Build, Execution, Deployment &gt; Build Tools &gt; Gradle&quot;. In there, you can set the JDK location.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qHtVe.png\" alt=\"Gradle Settings\" /></p>\n<p>To get your JDK location, run <code>/usr/libexec/java_home -v 11</code> in terminal. Send 1.7 for Java 7, 1.8 for Java 8, or 11 for Java 11.</p>\n"
